It was such an honor to premiere my drag alter ego Hersteria at Big Tits Bigger Dreams last weekend! Thank you @brigittebandit for putting on such an exciting, inclusive event and showing me that AFAB people can be drag queens in the first place. Thank you also to @__scamlikely__ for taking these amazing pictures and to @hejitsfrida for helping me do my makeup for the event, brainstorming ideas with me, and listening to my music 7,000 times through the walls of our house as I played it nonstop. A hundred years ago, I might be institutionalized for hysteria just for being the kind of person that I am and Hersteria is my personal project to advocate for people with mental illness, neurodivergence, and a variety of gender identities and expressions. I decided to do drag around the same time the news came out about New York’s new policy to detain people who seem mentally ill even if they’re not a danger to themselves or others and I want this project to be an exploration of how it would feel to exist without having to cover up or feel bad about anything about yourself that might be interpreted as mentally ill. It should be legal to be yourself in public, even if that self is different from the societal norm. I look forward to doing more shows as Hersteria and I’m so grateful for all the support I’ve already received. 🖤🖤

AUSTIN QUEERS AND PEOPLE WHO ARE COOL ENOUGH TO BE QUEER BUT JUST AREN’T FOR SOME REASON! Big Tits Bigger Dreams is back at Cheer Up Charlie’s tomorrow, Saturday February 4, 2023, and my drag queen alter ego Hersteria will be performing again! I had an amazing experience doing drag for the first time at this show last month so I’m going to be even more unhinged this month. Hope to see you there! Even if we barely know each other! You should come! The show is 7-9 at Cheer Up Charlie’s, followed by drinking rum and cokes and asking strangers if their power went out

first trip back to california since i accidentally moved to texas when i thought i was going to visit austin for a couple weeks and then never left 😅 so cool to hang out with @tomgalstian outside of a rave while at his wedding to @___kimberlyb 😊 how fucking cool. i also got to hang out with my family, play shuffleboard with @careington_17 and @nickman195, and wear uncomfortable shoes in front of some boats. i’m sorry to everyone i love in LA who i didn’t get to see this time, but don’t worry. california definitely reminded me that texas is a phase and i’ll come crawling back to her eventually. hopefully not literally. and hopefully after the flavored vape ban is overturned. i already had mango juul pods taken from me, i’m not ready to go through that kind of loss again. also, oliver. if you know you know ❤️

we live in scary and stressful times and the world needs us to step up and play our role in history. some of us are healthcare workers, saving lives. some of us are teachers, expanding minds. and me? i’m a drag queen who will be glamorous and mentally unstable onstage tomorrow night. come to Cheer Up Charlie’s for Big Tits Bigger Dreams because @brigittebandit puts on the most diverse drag show in texas and i’m going to look really good

My next single has a release date! Whenever I Die will be available for streaming and download on June 16 🖤 It was such an amazing feeling releasing Just World last June and hearing from people who really got the song and connected to it - I even sent it to Melvin Lerner, the sociologist who first identified and studied the just world fallacy in the 60s and received a lovely response from him approving of the song and my interpretation of his work. I did, however, discover the downside of making a song about a relatively obscure psychological phenomenon when some people didn’t realize the lyrics were satirical and took them as a personal endorsement of capitalism on my part (yikes). And as cool as it is to make meaningful art for a very specific audience, I know that if I want to grow my listener base I need to sing about more relatable topics! I took that lesson to heart so my second single, Whenever I Die, is a jam the whole family can enjoy about the time I did ketamine and k holed into another dimension where i saw the afterlife and cured my fear of death. It’s gonna be the song of the summer! #independentmusician #gothpop #edmproducer #singersongwriters
“I am not!” - Joanna Garcia Swisher, The Ultimatum: Queer Love, 2023 #ultimatumqueerlove #alienswatchingrealitytv

If you’re in Austin come to Cheer Up Charlie’s on Saturday to see me/Hersteria perform Whenever I Die and whether you’re in Austin or not I hope you follow me on Spotify and then listen to Whenever I Die when it comes out on June 16!
